    {
      "kind": "content",
      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "overview",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Overview",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "image",
              "identifier": "media-2929816",
              "metadata": {
                "anchor": "2929816",
                "title": "Figure 1",
                "abstract": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "A torus and its properties "
                  }
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": []
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "A torus is mathematically defined as a surface of revolution formed by revolving a circle around a coplanar axis. It is the product of two circles: a large ring and a pipe that encircles the ring. SceneKit uses these terms to define the dimensions of a torus geometry in its local coordinate space. The torus’ "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/scenekit/scntorus/1522906-ringradius"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " property defines a circle in the x- and z-axis dimensions, centered at the origin, and its "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/scenekit/scntorus/1522623-piperadius"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " property defines the width of the surface encircling the ring. To change the orientation of a torus, adjust the "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/scenekit/scnnode/1407964-transform"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " property of the node containing the torus geometry."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "Control the level of detail with the "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/scenekit/scntorus/1523598-ringsegmentcount"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " and "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/scenekit/scntorus/1522807-pipesegmentcount"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " properties. Higher segment counts produce more vertices and a more smoothly curved surface, which can improve rendering quality at a cost to rendering performance."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
